<div id="content">
          
		            
            <h1 class="page-title">The Halloween Event</h1>
            <p class="postmetadataw">Posted by: <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?author=1" title="Posts by admin" rel="author">admin</a> | on October 28, 2012</p> 
                        
            <div class="content-ver-sep"> </div>
            <div class="entrytext">			<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/spooky-event-title3.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-276" title="spooky event title3" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/spooky-event-title3.png" alt="" width="324" height="93" /></a></p>
<p>Here is some news about our Halloween Event: We have already reached our target of Koko donations!!! Great job you ghouls! And you are more than halfway there with your game scores…………</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/community-event4.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-373" title="community event4" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/community-event4.png" alt="" width="706" height="148" /></a></p>
<p>But time is running out to completely save ekoloko from Goliath Smog’s ghosts!!! <span style="color: #ff6600;"><strong>There are only 7 days left</strong></span> to continue playing our ghostly games and try and get those pumpkin-headed ghosts out of ekoloko for good!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/community-event3.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-370" title="community event3" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/community-event3.png" alt="" width="347" height="63" /></a></p>
<p>Click the <strong>Community Event button</strong> and join us to fight the evil pumpkins sent by Goliath Smog. We need you to help us reach our targets and you’ll get cool gifts along the way so keep going Ekos! All Ekos who help us reach our goal will get the ultimate treat! So remember – you gotta be IN IT to WIN IT!</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/news-title1.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-13" title="news title1" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/news-title1.png" alt="" width="349" height="104" /></a></p>
<p>This is not <strong>OUR</strong> Eko news but this is Cchen22’s ALMOST Eko news! So check it out:</p>
<p><a href="http://youtu.be/J8iAMZNEgf4" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','http://youtu.be']);">http://youtu.be/J8iAMZNEgf4</a></p>
<p>If you have things you’d like to share or send to the blog, please write to us at <a href="mailto:usa_blog@ekoloko.com">usa_blog@ekoloko.com</a> and we will be happy to include them (if we can).</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/jokes-title1.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-24" title="jokes title1" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/jokes-title1.png" alt="" width="250" height="87" /></a></p>
<p>Well, my sorry Ekos, since <strong>you</strong> did not come through with jokes for our corner, we got our own Megara to come up with some Halloween sillies that will have you giggling ghoulishly! So get ready to hold on to your head or it might fall off when you start laughing!!!</p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;">Question</span>: Why did Dracula take cold medicine?<br />
<span style="color: #ff6600;">Answer</span>: To get rid of his coffin.</p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;">Question</span>:  What is a ghost’s favorite kind of road?<br />
<span style="color: #ff6600;">Answer</span>: Dead Ends.</p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;">Question</span>:  What kind of mistakes do ghosts make?<br />
<span style="color: #ff6600;">Answer</span>: Boo Boos</p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;">Question</span>: Where do spooks mail their letters?<br />
<span style="color: #ff6600;">Answer</span>:  At the Ghost Office</p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;">Question</span>: Who won the Skeleton Beauty Contest?<br />
<span style="color: #ff6600;">Answer</span>:  No body.</p>
<p>Head still connected? If not, then get yourself together and send us YOUR jokes too! Send them to <a href="mailto:usa_blog@ekoloko.com">usa_blog@ekoloko.com</a> and write the word “Jokes” in the subject of your mail, and don’t forget your Eko name.</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/rangers-of-the-week-header.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-14" title="rangers of the week header" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/rangers-of-the-week-header.png" alt="" width="625" height="62" /></a></p>
<p>Enjoy some pictures of our Advanced Rangers ceremony last week:</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/ceremony2.png" ><img class="alignnone  wp-image-375" title="ceremony2" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/ceremony2.png" alt="" width="648" height="257" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/ceremony-donuts.png" ><img class="alignnone  wp-image-374" title="ceremony donuts" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/ceremony-donuts.png" alt="" width="474" height="250" /></a></p>
<p>If you were supposed to be at the ceremony but couldn’t make it at the scheduled time, please talk to a manager and another date will be arranged for you.</p>
<p>This week’s ceremony for Advanced Rangers will take place on two different days.</p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #000080;">On Wednesday, October 31st, at 3:30 PM Eastern Time</span></strong> (9:30 Europe and Israel time) we will have Ido450, Ponpon5560 and maybe Taleko</p>
<p><span style="color: #000080;"><strong>On Thursday, November 1<sup>st</sup>, at 3:30 PM Eastern Time </strong></span>our worthy rangers who will be getting their Advanced Ranger halos are: DanApple, mrnaia, Finder92 and Linkeko</p>
<p>Finally – there are lots and lots of new Ekos who need your help.</p>
<p>We wanted to remind you that the <span style="color: #008000;"><strong>BEST WAY</strong></span> to offer help is by INVITING new Ekos to play games with you, inviting them to see your moon house and offering to visit their houses and show them how to farm, and offering to take them around to see ekoloko or do quests.</p>
<p>Running around saying “Who needs help? I’m here to help you,” over and over is NOT what we mean by helping.</p>
<p>So get out there all you rangers, and rangers to be…and let’s make ekoloko USA the greatest place in the world!</p>
            </div>
